menu "Heap Allocator"

config HEAP_MEM
    bool "Enable dynamic heap memory allocator"
    default y
    help
      Enables vibe_heap_alloc() / vibe_heap_free() backed by a statically
      reserved heap region. The heap size is set by CONFIG_HEAP_SIZE.
      Disable to eliminate the heap entirely and save RAM.

config HEAP_SIZE
    int "Heap size in bytes"
    default 4096
    range 256 131072
    depends on HEAP_MEM
    help
      Size of the heap region in bytes. Must fit within available RAM after
      the kernel, stack, and static data are placed.
      Common values: 4096 (4 KB), 8192 (8 KB), 16384 (16 KB).

choice HEAP_ALLOCATOR
    prompt "Heap allocator algorithm"
    depends on HEAP_MEM
    default HEAP_ALLOCATOR_TLSF
    help
      Select the allocation algorithm used by vibe_heap_alloc() / vibe_malloc().

config HEAP_ALLOCATOR_TLSF
    bool "TLSF — Two-Level Segregated Fit (O(1) real-time)"
    help
      O(1) allocation and free. Uses a two-level bitmap to locate a suitable
      free block in constant time, with no loops or searching. Best choice for
      hard real-time systems or when allocation latency must be bounded.
      Control structure overhead: ~700 bytes (independent of heap size).

config HEAP_ALLOCATOR_BEST_FIT
    bool "Best Fit (O(n), lowest fragmentation)"
    help
      Scans all free blocks and picks the smallest one that fits the request.
      Minimises wasted space per allocation but requires a full list walk.
      Good when fragmentation matters more than allocation latency.

config HEAP_ALLOCATOR_FIRST_FIT
    bool "First Fit (O(n), lowest overhead)"
    help
      Returns the first free block large enough to satisfy the request.
      Simplest algorithm, lowest code size. Suitable for systems with
      predictable allocation patterns or very small heaps.

endchoice

config HEAP_STATS
    bool "Enable heap statistics"
    default y
    depends on HEAP_MEM
    help
      Enables vibe_heap_stats() to return live allocation metrics:
      total/used/free bytes, largest free block, alloc/free block counts.
      When disabled, vibe_heap_stats() fills the struct with zeros and
      the block-chain walk is omitted, saving cycles on every query.

config HEAP_CORRUPTION_CHECK
    bool "Enable heap corruption detection"
    default y
    depends on HEAP_MEM
    depends on !HEAP_ALLOCATOR_TLSF
    help
      Verifies magic values in block headers on every vibe_heap_free() to
      detect double-frees and out-of-bounds writes. Adds one comparison per
      free call and prints a diagnostic if corruption is detected.
      Not applicable to the TLSF backend (TLSF uses its own size-flag checks).
      Disable to remove the check on performance-critical paths.

endmenu
